items.title: Army in full control of Khartoum, Sudan military leader says
items.description: "Khartoum is free," says army chief Abdel Fattah al-Burhan after almost two years of occupation by the RSF.

items.title: Hundreds join Gaza's largest anti-Hamas protest since war began
items.description: Masked Hamas militants dispersed protesters who gathered in northern Gaza to rally against the group.

items.title: Russia says sanctions must be lifted before Ukraine maritime ceasefire can start
items.description: Moscow and Kyiv appear at odds over when and how the US-brokered deal will come into effect.

items.title: Brazil's Bolsonaro to stand trial on coup charges, court rules
items.description: Brazil's top court has ruled that there is enough evidence to warrant that Jair Bolsonaro be put on trial.

items.title: Trump names conservative media critic as US ambassador to South Africa
items.description: Brent Bozell's nomination comes at a time when relations between South Africa and the United States are at a low point.
